-- TABLE-Hong Kong yuan deposits fall 3.1 pct in June vs May
-- By Michelle Chen and Christina Lo
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 05:12AM EDT
-- None



July 31 (Reuters) - Yuan deposits in Hong Kong, an offshore market for the Chinese currency, fell to 925.9 billion yuan ($149.97 billion) in June, down 3.1 percent from a month earlier, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority said on Thursday.

Cross-border trade settled in yuan rose 19.8 percent in June to 531.8 billion yuan on a month-on-month basis.  The following are yuan deposit data:Hong Kong Deposits:Jun   May   Apr   Mar   Feb   Jan   Yuan (or Rmb bln) 925.9 955.8 959.9 944.9 920.3 893.4   pct change m/m -3.1  -0.4   1.6   2.7   3.0   3.8 pct of total deposits  12.1  12.5  12.7  12.8  12.3  12.3 Total (HK$ bln)   9,612 9,522 9,392 9,189  9,330 9,184Total yuan remittances for cross-border trade settlement (through Hong Kong's banking system):